08/08/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Milorad Jelisavac, Republika Srpska's head of criminal police, said at a news conference in Banja Luka Thursday (7 August) that crime rates were increasing. 
Despite police efforts, he said, the number of robberies increased by 10 per cent in the first half of the year, compared to a year earlier. 
Jelisavac criticised the institutions in the country and the region for insufficient co-operation in fighting organised crime. 
(SRNA - 07/08/03)
